    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Traditional one side edged swords of various tribes in Indonesia. Initially intended as a cleaver, and later used as a weapon. Dutch troops in Indonesia also called their modified cutlasses by this name. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
